[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m considering that adding reflection to a private method may require metadata generated by the agent. If they run natively after that, the test using reflection should generate the metadata on the JVM. The native image configuration includes test resources without modifications, which could complicate things. I’m thinking about removing the original exerciseCached to minimize risk. The patched loader runs only under isolated paths on the JVM, and I want to ensure native tests pass without causing any issues. Should I remove the exerciseCachedDirectBufferConstructor entirely?
